==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}}, {{m|enm|abecedary}}, from {{etyl|ML.|en}} {{m|la|abecedarium||alphabet, primer}}, from {{etyl|LL.|en}} {{m|la|abecedarius||of the alphabet}}, formed from the first four letters of the Latin alphabet + {{m|la|-arius|}}.

The sense "primer, abecearium" is from {{etyl|ML.|en}} {{m|la|abecedarium||alphabet, primer}}.<ref name=SOED>{{R:SOED5|page=3}}</ref>

